Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.64,0:00:05.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}From a different point of view, even an imposing\Nwall blocking your path is just a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.15,0:00:08.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(200,300,\c&HB8C1CD&)}A character from a mystery novel\Nthreatens the life of its author.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:09.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HB8C1CD&}Is this fiction, or non-fiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HB8C1CD&\t(200,300,\c&HFFAAAA)}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.19,0:00:12.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HFFAAAA}and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.82,0:00:14.66,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HFFAAAA}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,How to Win at Horse Racing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.97,0:02:01.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Pro Football, 2006
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.71,0:02:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm being called!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.90,0:02:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.27,0:02:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Coming through!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems it's my turn. Let's go!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Wait! Inspector!\N- Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.68,0:02:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure seem to have a lot of free time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.93,0:02:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since we're here anyway, please let us help with the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, this brat might cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.68,0:02:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Inspector, what kind of case is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.46,0:02:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.24,0:02:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is the person who lived in this flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 65.{uso: probably edit to "Murako Saikawa, age 65?"}\NShe lived alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently she was a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.26,0:02:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does the name sound familiar, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murako Saikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I seem to recall that long ago, there was a novelist by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.82,0:03:13.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Murako Saikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:17.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An incredible mystery novelist,\Nfamous for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Death was instantaneous, caused by\Na blow to the head with a decorative object.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what was determined\Nduring the investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.30,0:03:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she was murdered last night,\Napproximately between 7 and 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might get a more accurate estimated time of death once the autopsy is concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.93,0:03:37.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who'd want to murder a famous mystery novelist, and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the body was found by two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Tono.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I work at Labyrinth Publications,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.60,0:03:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I was Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.33,0:03:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is the block of flats' manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Murata.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:03:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us again exactly\Nhow you found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, I went over\Nto pick up some documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.06,0:04:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I met up with her yesterday, we'd agreed I'd come by to pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.46,0:04:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, no matter how often I kept ringing the intercom, nobody came to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt that was kind of strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.55,0:04:16.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I asked the manager to use his key to open the door for me, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.33,0:04:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.77,0:04:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were at Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s home yesterday, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.62,0:04:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I was there from early in the evening until around 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:35.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The estimated time of death was between 7 and 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you've got really great instincts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd that you knew something was up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just because nobody answered the intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really does sound strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's because a couple of days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.37,0:04:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei received this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A postcard...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:05:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.42,0:05:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the next piece I will be adding to my collection will be your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will come to take it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.06,0:05:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A death threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.51,0:05:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was sent by a... Taniyoshi Ohebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's read Ryo Orochiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.54,0:05:20.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ryo Orochiya? That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this Ryo Orochiya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.97,0:05:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a criminal mastermind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s biggest novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.72,0:05:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The novelist was murdered by a character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!\NThat's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that does seem to be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.69,0:05:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a trick by the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.13,0:05:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did it to confuse the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:48.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To confuse the investigators?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.68,0:05:51.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But was that the only objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you have an empty flat, we'd appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.26,0:05:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd like to use it as a base of operations for our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you may have been the last person to see the victim alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.35,0:06:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you stay with\Nus for a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.91,0:06:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.72,0:06:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said the flat was locked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose the killer left it locked last night, before escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, they could delay the time it took to find the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But from what I understand, in this block, each tenant gets two keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s two keys were found inside the flat, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.46,0:06:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the killer have a copy of the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.20,0:06:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. That means there's a limited number of people who could've used such a key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor who came to meet her might have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.43,0:06:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he could've had one made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the manager has one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.95,0:07:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was Kawanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, he just finished interrogating all the neighbours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.20,0:07:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, a few days ago, the victim\Nand the manager had a very heated row.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They seem to be our main suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.91,0:07:24.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tono{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who was visiting the victim up until the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:26.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And Murata{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},\Nwho had a potential motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.73,0:07:30.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Furthermore, either of them could've had a copy of the key made.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.72,0:07:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, if either of them is the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then it's no coincidence that they were the ones who found the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By being the first to arrive,\Nthe killer could've come inside
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and got rid of any evidence he might've left the previous night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.60,0:07:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.42,0:08:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just remnants of ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} hated fresh ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.91,0:08:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She always said she couldn't\Nstand its bittersweet taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose she took all of the ginger from the sushi she ordered last night, and threw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.51,0:08:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She ordered sushi for dinner last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, she asked me for it,\Nand I ordered it over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we have the entire floor available for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.23,0:08:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please tell us everything that happened last night, in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.97,0:08:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:36.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she threw it away last night,\Nthen it's been over half a day since.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:39.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In that case, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed\Nbetween 7 and 9pm yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I arrived to see her at around 6:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.91,0:08:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though she wasn't doing it\Nprofessionally anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she still kept writing a lot of mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were together for about an hour, talking about the possibility of publishing them all as a collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.27,0:09:07.94,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, Saikawa.\NAt the Pearl block of flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.94,0:09:09.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The usual order, for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.00,0:09:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The order arrived at around 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.03,0:09:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had other business\Nto deal with, I left afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:22.17,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll come to pick up the documents\Ntomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.17,0:09:23.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.40,0:09:25.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you'll excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.04,0:09:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around a quarter to 9, I met up with some friends in front of the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stayed with them\Nuntil deep into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until deep into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll confirm this with your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.93,0:09:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm perfectly aware that I'm a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.86,0:09:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a treasure\Namong mystery novelists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a row with Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People must've misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be the case.\NEither way, tell me about last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the manager's quarters the whole time. {unsure, please check –Putoずっと管理人室に。 It's about right. zutto would probably be interpreted "the whole time". -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.31,0:10:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was alone, so I don't have any witness to confirm it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.33,0:10:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manager's hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key point is at 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 7 to 8, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could've committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after 8, it could've been Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, split up and investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.27,0:10:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.94,0:10:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were told she ordered\Nsushi from here last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.33,0:10:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! How could I screw up this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.28,0:10:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll pay for this for my entire life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.03,0:10:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you explain what you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.15,0:10:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and the octopus!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.87,0:10:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and the octopus?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.42,0:10:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, in our restaurant, we don't include squid or octopus in our orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.48,0:11:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}\Nordered them, we always did,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.73,0:11:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they were her favourite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But last night, I was careless and forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, was that it?\NI thought it was something serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it was serious!\NIt was her last order!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just came to ask when\Nyou took the order to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.22,0:11:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.41,0:11:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.57,0:11:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took the order to her flat at 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.17,0:11:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he didn't see Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} anywhere, and didn't hear her talk, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, she was already in the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.15,0:11:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't, editor-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.32,0:11:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the editor-in-chief of Labyrinth Publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:11:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Shimazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.68,0:12:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was told Tono is one of your suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.15,0:12:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.66,0:12:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came to work for us,\Nspecialising in mystery novels,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.40,0:12:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he admired\NSaikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s work so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.91,0:12:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even today, he was planning the\Npublication of a collection of her works!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.83,0:12:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.67,0:12:20.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A true fan of Murako Saikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you familiar with Murako Saikawa's works?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.93,0:12:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not until this case came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, because\Nshe's been forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's precisely why he insisted her works should be published.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.15,0:12:38.02,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's tons of people who don't know the greatness of Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-sensei{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:41.03,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Original tricks, perfect composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.03,0:12:46.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I want everyone in Japan to know of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.66,0:12:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I didn't think it'd sell well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.13,0:12:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our publisher{confirm term please –Puto} is in a precarious situation.{うちの経営は　いつも火の車です。経営 [けいえい] /(n,vs) management/administration/(P)/}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And publishing something with low sales expectations would only make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:12:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think we'd do it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.79,0:13:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was moved by his passionate desire\Nto make her happy during her final days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.06,0:13:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her final days?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.01,0:13:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doctor said she had an incurable illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had, at most, half a year to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.47,0:13:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono is the one who'd regret Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s passing the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.75,0:13:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.04,0:13:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Beika Medical University. {the catalan didn't say Beika, but I'm hearing it in the jp so added it –Puto医大 [いだい] /(n) (abbr) medical university/medical school/med school/(P)/prolly good enough -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.11,0:13:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got the autopsy results back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.44,0:13:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's stomach contained rice and raw fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And apparently she was killed an hour later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.88,0:13:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the order was taken to her at 8pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the estimated time of death would be around 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.10,0:13:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as far as Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:14:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we've confirmed that he was with his friends the whole night, starting at a quarter to nine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.90,0:14:04.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His alibi checks out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies for having suspected you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.80,0:14:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can leave now, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.42,0:14:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad, Tono.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.04,0:14:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.11,0:14:16.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What? You saw him last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.02,0:14:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I had to make a delivery at a specific time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that's when I saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was around 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,9pm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.93,0:14:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like to drink a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:41.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one day, old Saikawa saw me sipping a bit in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd inform\Nthe management company.{She said she was gonna inform the block of flats' management companyterm is probably wrong. –Puto.管理会社に報告するとかって...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.19,0:14:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be joking, I'd get fired for sure if that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.11,0:14:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I went to visit her last night, to ask her to reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no matter how much I kept ringing the intercom, that old lady wouldn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.70,0:15:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you suspect me, show me the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.97,0:15:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stinks of alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.40,0:15:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll open the window, to bring in some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.98,0:15:20.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course! There's another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:22.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And there's also that ginger...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.19,0:15:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Proof... Proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:36.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I figured out the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:44.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I figured out the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:46.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But what was the motive?{LTIL: But why did that person... -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.21,0:15:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.80,0:15:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among the things found at the crime scene, there's nothing that indicates Mr Murata{isn't it -shi? -uso} as the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.46,0:15:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on the news now.\NIt's super-sensational.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.11,0:16:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably made a ton of cash off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Famous Novelist Gets a Death Threat from a Character in Her Novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couldn't keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.84,0:16:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even revealed all the info about the postcard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.82,0:16:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of an ongoing investigation are supposed to be a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.51,0:16:23.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.35,0:16:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.60,0:16:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it the usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.97,0:16:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've solved everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi! Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.68,0:16:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.55,0:16:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the killer used an alibi trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.73,0:16:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An alibi trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.12,0:17:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's put the case's facts in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.57,0:17:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed\Nbetween 7 and 9pm yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it happened approximately one hour after she ate the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.63,0:17:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Therefore, the approximate time of death is 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where the problem lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.57,0:17:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was that determined?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the sushi order\Nwas taken to her at 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.95,0:17:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but the sushi inside Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nstomach wasn't necessarily {\i1}that specific sushi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.33,0:17:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.62,0:17:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition to the order of sushi that was sent to her at 8pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} visited her,\Nhe also brought some sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i1}actually{\i0} ate the sushi that Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.92,0:17:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't after 8, but at 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.06,0:17:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An hour later, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.86,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that point, digestion\Nstopped in the victim's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would prove that she was killed an hour after she ate the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called the sushi restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.95,0:18:10.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The usual order, for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:12.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you for your patronage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:17.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stored the sushi that arrived\Nat 8 inside a plastic bag,{jp: vinyl is a wasei-eigo}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.53,0:18:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,locked the door with a copy of the key,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.24,0:18:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to ensure the body\Nwasn't found immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.12,0:18:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and halfway through, he threw away the bag with the sushi and the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, he was able to set up\Nan alibi for 8:45 onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew that sooner or later, an autopsy would reveal that she died an hour after eating sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.33,0:18:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And given the call to the sushi restaurant at 8pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, we thought the time of death was 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result of that, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had an alibi for that time, would no longer be a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.17,0:18:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is to say, he used the autopsy that was intended to help solve the case, in order to set up an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you made a mistake. The ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that ginger was from last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would've dried up long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But somehow, the ginger we found was still soft...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because last night, when you disposed of the sushi you ordered, you also disposed of the ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, you realised your mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,asked Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to open the door for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when the manager wasn't looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.93,0:19:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you slipped that ginger into the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.22,0:19:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop this! Where are you getting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.73,0:19:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gave her sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that Sensei ate the same sushi that was taken to her at eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, according to the autopsy,\Nwhat did they find in Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was sushi, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but more specifically?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:19:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.93,0:20:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rice, tuna, sea urchin,\Nflounder, squid, octopus...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Squid and octopus?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, doesn't it sound strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.93,0:20:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.97,0:20:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.56,0:20:17.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, no! How could I screw up this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.57,0:20:20.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The squid and the octopus!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.07,0:20:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He forgot them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.48,0:20:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew exactly the kind of sushi she would like, and therefore, didn't forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and octopus that she loved so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.26,0:20:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were shocked that the restaurant owner forgot them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The autopsy you manipulated,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.80,0:20:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ended up turning against you, and brought you to your doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.53,0:20:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the end of the line for you, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.11,0:20:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beginning with Ryo Orochiya, every criminal that Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} created
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.56,0:20:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,accepted their guilt when\Nthey were caught, did they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.22,0:20:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you do it, Tono?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.33,0:21:02.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei was ill, and had very little time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.31,0:21:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if she died from an illness,\Nshe would've done so as a forgotten novelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and nobody would have\Npaid any attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.37,0:21:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if she was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.51,0:21:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and by a character from the novels she herself wrote at that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.57,0:21:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the media would make a big deal out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted the world to know who Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.53,0:21:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you came up with that strange death threat, and caused all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.71,0:21:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever the motive, there's {\i1}never{\i0} a justification for murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.27,0:21:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for her sake, it was better...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.27,0:21:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really do this just for Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.27,0:21:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this came out in the media, the collection of her works would sell a lot more,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.33,0:21:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the publisher would profit greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.06,0:21:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you consider that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted Labyrinth Publications to continue working on mystery novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.87,0:21:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono... God damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:21:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.40,0:22:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A person who truly loves mystery novels would {\i1}never{\i0} commit murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, they changed to a different manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.53,0:23:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.06,0:23:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A manager who spends the entire day drinking is in no condition to work properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.53,0:23:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Down it goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.68,0:24:03.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(2302,3804,\c&H000000&\3c&H000000&)}What about a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, if everybody\Nhas a red handkerchief,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.54,0:24:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's no way to tell\Nwhich one's yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:16.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? A notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:17.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.40,0:24:20.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a bloodstain on the planner.
